<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-HOFFARTH-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LET'S WAIT BEFORE SIZING RINGS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ All Kurt Rambis should have to do at this point in
the roller-coaster ride is unfurl one of those ``You Are Here''
maps in the Lakers locker room that shows a path starting at the
Forum and ending on the steps of City Hall with a buncha rings
drawn around it.
</P>
<P>
   But this is the !ital!Lakers we're talkin' about here.
</P>
<P>
   Swattin' away one-point wins on the home court against a team
whose average age is older than the L.A. Sports Arena popcorn ain't
nothing to be chest-thumpin' about.
</P>
<P>
   Save it for late June. If there is one. Then we'll praise you
like we should....
</P>
<P>
   The other day, Yankees owner George Steinbrenner and Nets
co-owner Lewis Katz went before an NBA finance committee to explain
the proposed merger of the two teams' business operations. Lakers
sugardaddy Jerry Buss was quoted as saying: ``I'm just trying to
understand it.''
</P>
<P>
   Funny, but that's what Jerry West said to the Doc when he
rubber-stamped the D.Rodman acquisition....
</P>
<P>
   If L.A. decides it really wants an NFL expansion team, John
Elway would be the guy to lead the charge. 'Cause you know as that
Sept. 15 deadline comes near, and still nuthin' is done, they're
gonna need someone to save everyone's rear ends and pull out a
miracle....
</P>
<P>
   Aside from L.A.'s seemingly vested interest, isn't the best
reason not to add a 32nd team to the NFL is because it'll water
down a product that seems to be hydroplaning quite well on its own
at this point?
</P>
<P>
   When it gets to 40, sell....
</P>
<P>
   Chicago Bears offensive coordinator Gary Crownton said it about
6-foot-1 rookie QB Cade McNown, who some believe is too short to
play in the NFL: ``He's about the size of a lot of guys that
size.''...
</P>
<P>
   Before they drafted McNown, da Bears were all set to sign free
agent Todd Marinovich. Lookin' around, Toddie's next bet might
be... L.A.'s new arena team?...
</P>
<P>
   Further proof Gifferoo will !ital!never live this down, the
cover of the June issue of McCall's is ``A frank talk with Kathie
Lee: How she's survived the ultimate betrayal.''...
</P>
<P>
   Fox's Howie Long made it into People magazine's issue of ``The
50 Most Beautiful People In the World 1999.''
</P>
<P>
   Foxes Catherine Zeta-Jones, Ashley Judd, Katie Holmes, Charlize
Theron, Rebecca Gayheart, Tyra Banks (and the rest of Victoria
Secret's spring '99 catalog, for that matter), Cameron Diaz, Daisy
Fuentes, Salma Hayek, Alyssa Milano, Kate Moss, Denise Richards,
Jenna Jameson, Courteney Cox, Courtney Love _ not, Ali Landry (she
flips for Doritos in the commercial), Heather Graham, Heather
