   8. AL GORE'S MONEY MACHINE When it comes to campaign
fund-raising, Al Gore is known as ``one of the best closers in the
business'' - especially in relation to Bill Clinton, who hates to
ask for money. And the vice president by now has raked in record
millions to support his quest for the presidency. But his talent
for fundraising could prove a dangerous habit. By Jill Abramson.
