</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eds: Runs with NFK-NEWSFLASH and NFK-FEATURE
 &HT;    Check it out
 &HT;    News for Kids
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Be a hardhead
</P>
<P>
   TV's ``Sabrina the Teenage Witch'' wants you to know that more
than 200 kids die each year from bike crashes. A lot of those
deaths and injuries could be prevented if kids wore helmets while
riding. To learn more about bike safety and to play some cool
Shockwave games, head to www
</P>
<P>
   .bikehelmet.org. You can test your helmet IQ, state your
opinion, chat online with other kids about bikes, send a friend a
bike card and color cool biking scenes. Plus, navigate the Canyon
Trail Obstacle Course and try your hand at the Xtra Xtreme Cranium
Canyon Bike Race.
</P>
<P>
   Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
</P>
<P>
   Your town can be Matchbox USA
</P>
<P>
   Do you love the town where you live? Would you like some money
to buy new playground equipment or new books for your local
library? If you can convince Matchbox in 50 words or less or with a
great drawing that your town should be named Matchbox USA, you
could win $25,000 for a community program. Plus, the name of your
town will be featured on Matchbox police cars, ambulances and fire
trucks. The essays will be judged on originality and civic need.
You must be 14 or under to enter. Official entries and contest
rules can be found at www.matchboxtoys.com or by calling
1-800-524-TOYS (8697).
</P>
<P>
   _ Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
</P>
<P>
   Giarrusso writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
