direction of any tsunami they might produce. But this is fraught
with errors caused by unknown variables such as the topography of
the seabed. ``The idea of using a buoy may seem obvious, but it has
only been made possible because of recent advances in GPS
technology,'' says Teruyuki Kato of Tokyo University's Earthquake
Research Institute.
