u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX     05-10 0701
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TEXBUDGET-TEX </SLUG>
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Fort Worth Star-Telegram plans to move the following stories
for clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs of Tuesday, May 11,
and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Tom Uhler,
Lou Hudson, Paul Wagner or Jim Peipert on the Star-Telegram's
National/Foreign Desk at (817) 390-7785. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   W A S H I N G T O N &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ARTS-FOUNDATION &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The arts community, stung by cutbacks in federal
arts programs and the virtual elimination of grants to individual
artists, is stepping into the breach with a grants program of its
own. Tuesday, a group of arts patrons and 22 arts organizations are
to announce the formation of the Creative Capital Foundation,
organizers said. By MARIA RECIO. Story has moved in ``w''
Washington category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   N A T I O N A L &QL; 
