1979, in Wichita Falls, Texas. The day a mammoth tornado cut an
8-mile-long swath through the city, killing 45 people, injuring
1,702 and leaving 20,000 homeless. It was strikingly similar to the
tornadoes that demolished parts of Oklahoma City and nearby towns
last week, killing more than 40 people, flattening houses and
shredding the landscape. By D'ANN MABRAY SHIPPY. Story will move in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
