receive from abortion providers. By Karen Hsu. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LYCOS-USANET (Undated) _ Lycos executives now doubt shareholders
would approve the proposed merger with elements of USA Networks
Inc., setting the stage for further negotatiations. By Ross Kerber
and Hiawatha Bray. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   FLEET-BANKBOS (Boston) _ In key executive appointments that show
their proposed $8 billion merger is not one of equals but rather
one of two distinctly different banks with varying strengths, Fleet
and BankBoston decide the fates of 50 senior officials. By Lynnley
Browning. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   CNN-HILL-HOLLIDAY (Boston) _ Hill Holliday Connors Cosmopulos
becomes the ad agency of record for CNN as Fidelity hires another
ad agency to help Hill Holliday market the mutual funds giant. By
Chris Reidy. 500 words.
</P>
