  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of May
11 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BKN-LAKERS (Inglewood, Calif.) _ Advance to Game 2 of the Los
Angeles Lakers-Houston Rockets playoff series focusing on how to
stop Charles Barkley. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBA-KAPWEAV (New York) _ Gabe Kapler from Taft High School in Los
Angeles and Jeff Weaver from Simi Valley, Calif., were long shots
to make it to the major leagues. And yet, both are flourishing in
their first year with the Detroit Tigers. 
By Joe Haakenson/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles Dodgers play host to the
Chicago Cubs, 7:10 p.m. Sammy Sosa makes his first visit to Dodger
Stadium this season. Sosa has seven home runs this season for the
14-14 Cubs. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBA-BELCHER (New York) _ Tim Belcher was supposed to help shore up
the Anaheim Angels' starting pitching, come up with 10-15 victories
and give the team plenty of quality innings. Instead, Belcher has
struggled this season, rarely making it out of the fifth inning.
His ERA is hovering around 10.00, his ball lacks movement and
opponents are lighting him up. 
By Joe Haakenson/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
