<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Tuesday, May 11. If you
have
<TEXT>
<P>
   any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Y2K HOTELS (Phoenix) - Father time wears a Rolex this New Year's
Eve and free-spending partiers might wake up in the new millennium
with a Dom Perignon-like hangover. Four nights at the MGM Grand and
Barbra singing `The Way We Were` (Before We Were Broke) at a Jan.
31 show is $8,500. The Phoenician's seven-night package is $6,600
per couple. The Arizona Biltmore is bringing in the Righteous Bros.
and the Temptations on back to back nights in a package that ranges
from $7,000 to $15,000. By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
TV-CULTURE-COMMENT (Phoenix) - If you dislike certain trends in
music or movies or lifestyle or belief patterns, you don't have to
engage them. You have a free choice to accept anything, or reject
anything. Such is the blessing of a free society. On the face of
things, this is obviously true.
</P>
<P>
   But _ and this is the thing usually forgotten _ I cannot choose
to live in a culture that is free of the elements I reject. If I
don't like what's currently acceptable, I have the right to attempt
to change it through art, through protest, through educational
reform. ``Turning off the television'' is not only not enough, it
simply isn't possible. By KENNETH LAFAVE. Story moved in the ``L''
and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STARHISTORY-MOVIES (Phoenix) - Before ``Star Wars,'' there were
spaceships hanging from strings in ``Plan 9 From Outer Space.''
</P>
<P>
   Before ``Star Wars,'' science fiction was sci-fi as far as
Hollywood was concerned; B-movie throwaways for the underside of a
Saturday matinee double bill for kids. ``Star Wars'' changed all
that. With STARGUIDE. By BOB FENSTER. Story moved in the ``E''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
STARGUIDE-MOVIES (Phoenix) - ``Star Wars'' wasn't the first great
science fiction movie. Here are 10 winners that brought worlds of
SF to the screen before Wookiees were a gleam in George Lucas' eye.
And
</P>
<P>
   here are five imaginative works of science fiction that you
might have missed since the original ``Star Wars.'' Story also
includes a list of recommended SF books. With STARHISTORY-MOVIES.
By BOB FENSTER. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SCIFI-'50S-MOVIES (Phoenix) - ``Star Wars,'' Star Snores.
</P>
<P>
   Can't compare with ``Devil Girl From Mars.'' Those of us who
grew up on the real thing know that if you want the bona fides, you
must find them in the mustier corners of your video store or the
back channels of your basic cable.
</P>
<P>
   For the kind of sci-fi that sticks to your frontal lobe for a
lifetime, you're talking the 1950s. With lists of '50s movies. By
RICHARD NILSEN. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WILSON-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ A compelling letter arrived last week
from an American soldier in the Balkans, calling our air campaign
against Serbia illegal, immoral and illogical. Because he didn't
know a relative would give the letter to a journalist, I won't
quote him; publicizing his words could have the unhappy consequence
of a court-martial. But since his views and mine happen to run
parallel, I'll quote myself. BY STEVE WILSON. Story moved in the
``K'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
