<P>
   WHALE-HUNT (Neah Bay, Wash.) _ The Makah tribe conducts its
first whale hunt in 70 years, and the first legal whale hunt in the
United States in decades. So far the hunt has fizzled as the
migrating gray whales play cat and mouse with the whalers.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Sunde and Michael Barber. (Story will move in the ``a''
category.)
</P>
<P>
   AMAZON-PRIVACY (Seattle) _ Amazon.com has leapt into many happy
investors' portfolios by selling more books online than anyone
else. The world's largest Internet retailer may now be poised to
start trading in a more controversial item: Personal information on
its customers.
</P>
