award-winning tree farm at the Yale Forest Forum. He followed-up
his talk with a version of ``Route 66'' on the baby grand. (Dominic
Chavez/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) LOS ALAMOS, N.M. -- May 10, 1999 --
SCI-SPY-SAFEHOUSE-B&AMP;W, 5-10 -- The atomic age began with this
explosion on July 16, 1945 in the New Mexico desert. At bottom is
an aerial view of the crater created by the blast. Researchers have
uncovered materials showing that espionage was already well under
way by the Soviets in order to develop their own bomb. (New York
Times Photo) LITE
</P>
