<HEADLINE>
CITIFIED GINGHAM 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thanks to designers like Karl Lagerfeld for Chanel and Stella
McCartney for Chloe, gingham is no longer restricted to country
picnics but has taken on a sophisticated look for spring.
</P>
<P>
   Bergdorf Goodman has Chanel's filmy checked dance dress
($3,795), Chloe's shirt ($610) and clamdiggers ($590), Tocca's
spaghetti-strap dress ($165) and matching bag ($130), Strenesse's
sleeveless shirt ($200) and several bags by Kate Spade ($185 to
$230).
</P>
<P>
   Saks Fifth Avenue has a short-sleeved shirtdress by A.B.S.
($145), an embroidered party dress by Mica ($128) and platform
slides by Moschino Cheap and Chic ($270).
</P>
<P>
   Neiman Marcus has two Tocca designs in red-and-white gingham: a
halter dress and a sundress ($170 each).
</P>
<P>
   CK Calvin Klein has used pink-and-white gingham for long-sleeved
nightshirts ($39), short-sleeved pajama tops and long pajama pants
($35 each) and drawstring boxer shorts ($23), all at Lord &AMP; Taylor.
</P>
</TEXT>
